# Why Cats Are Awesome

A non-exhaustive case for the defense.

- **Self-installing.** Plug in food and water. They handle the rest.
<!-- pause -->
- **Quiet.** Average bark output: zero per day.
<!-- pause -->
- **Pest control.** A cat removes more rodents per week than three traps and a bored terrier combined.
<!-- pause -->
- **Heated.** Body temperature 38.5В°C. Doubles as a lap warmer in winter.
<!-- pause -->
- **Independently funded.** Will hunt their own snacks if the opportunity arises.

<!-- note: Don't rush through these. Each one gets a beat. The "self-installing" line lands hardest if you wait for the laugh. -->
