# Cat Communication

Cats have ~21 distinct vocalizations.

<!-- pause -->

| Sound       | Meaning                          | Audience       |
|-------------|----------------------------------|----------------|
| Meow        | "Hello human"                    | Humans only    |
| Trill       | Friendly greeting                | Humans + cats  |
| Purr        | Contentment OR self-soothing     | Anyone nearby  |
| Chatter     | "I see prey"                     | Self           |
| Hiss        | "Back off"                       | Threats        |
| Yowl        | Mating, distress, or 3am opinion | Whole building |

<!-- pause -->

> Adult cats almost never meow at *each other*. The meow is a vocalization domestic cats developed specifically to communicate with humans.

<!-- note: This is the most "learn something new" moment of the talk. Make sure the blockquote is on screen long enough to read. -->

