# The Math of Cuteness

A toy model.

```
cuteness = (eye_sizeВІ Г— softness) / dignity
```

<!-- pause -->

Where:

- `eye_size` is normalized to a logarithmic scale
- `softness` is measured in microfibers per cmВІ
- `dignity` is the only term that *increases* with age

<!-- pause -->

> A kitten maximizes cuteness because its dignity term is near zero. An old cat has high dignity but compensates with sheer cumulative charisma.

---variant: cuteness-equation-tighter
# The Cuteness Equation

```
cuteness = (eyesВІ Г— fluff) / dignity
```

Three terms. The denominator is the only one you can't fix.

---variant: cuteness-equation-no-math
# Why Kittens Win

Kittens are dignity-poor and eye-rich. Adults trade eye-richness for dignity. Both are good. The kittens are louder about it.

<!-- ai: 2 variants on slide 9. the first ("tighter") is the same idea shorter. the second ("no-math") drops the equation entirely for audiences that glaze over at math. test variant switching here when working on the variant UI. -->

